I"ò<p>During <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/skill-acquisition-spans-cognitive-associative-autonomous-stages">skill acquisition</a>, the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tacit-knowledge-in-skill-acquisition-is-dark-knowledge-in-machine-learning">learner</a> reaches a stage where they can only reliably <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/skill-exchanges-can-work-like-torrents">use the skill</a> under <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/predictive-models-capture-expert-uncertainty-in-process-mining">expert guidance</a>. Until then, the skill is said to be in the zone of proximal development of the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/validation-through-creation-quantifies-free-learning">learner</a>.</p>
